{"id":"2107.12426","submitter":"Jordi Delgado","authors":"Jordi Delgado, Mallika Roy, Enric Ventura","title":"Intersection configurations in free and free times free-abelian groups","comments":"19 pages, 8 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.GR","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In this paper we delve into the behaviour of multiple intersections of\nsubgroups of free and free times free-abelian (FTFA) groups with respect to\nfinite generability.\n  It is well known that free groups satisfy the Howson property (the\nintersection of any two finitely generated subgroups is again finitely\ngenerated). We show that Howson property is indeed the only obstruction for\nmultiple intersection configurations to be realizable within $\\mathbb{F}_n$.\n  On the contrary, FTFA groups are well known to be non-Howson. We study\nmultiple intersections within FTFA groups, and we give an algorithm to decide,\ngiven $k\\geqslant 2$ finitely generated subgroups, whether their intersection\nis again finitely generated and, in the affirmative case, compute a basis for\nit. We also show that any finite intersection configuration is realizable in\n$\\mathbb{F}_n \\times \\mathbb{Z}^m$, for $n\\geqslant 2$ and $m$ big enough. As a\nconsequence, we exhibit a finitely presented group where every intersection\nconfiguration is realizable.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 26 Jul 2021 18:34:26 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 3 Aug 2022 15:00:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-04"}
